Message-ID: <CAOCiBRf0EAxkDmwXbf3P8gKqWbCLOHfEwLK=zoVCrOzC=fQJ2Q@mail.gmail.com>

When you use Cuda, make sure your GPU can handle the current version of
Cuda C and that you have enough ram on your GPU to handle the amount of
data you are processing. Also be aware that most Cuda programs use float,
not double float. That can lead you to vastly different answers if you are
using an iterative process.

